h3. Problem Definition
As per latest [JIRA Service Desk 2.6.0-OD-10 release|https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/23-august-2015-to-29-august-2015-777010089.html]

{quote}
We've been working on automated responses in Service Desk, and in this release we've tweaked the wording of the default set of notifications to make them a little friendlier. We've also decreased the number of default notifications sent to service desk customers, and updated the format in which notifications are sent.
{quote}

h3. Suggested Solution
* Revert the previous HTML format for JIRA Service Desk Notification. 
* Additionally, support adding a comment when they are replied on.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2366].
  {panel}

