We would like to add more operations under the "You can" section of the Customer Portal. For instance, we want to add operations that would allow the Customer to "Escalate" the issue.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2344].
  {panel}

h3. Problem Definition 

Having a report to show JIRA Service Desk administrator which channel issues are created from.
This is to track user adoption of Service Desk. It would be beneficial to be able to see if Agents are creating tickets themselves, customers are sending requests via email, or customers are creating tickets via the JIRA Service Desk Customer Portal.

h3. Workaround

{code:title=To filter tickets from E-mail|borderStyle=solid}
issue.property["request.channel.type"].value = "email"
{code}

{code:title=To filter tickets from JIRA Service Desk Customer Portal|borderStyle=solid}
issue.property["request.channel.type"].value = "portal"
{code}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2342].
  {panel}

h3. Problem Definition 

At https://confluence.atlassian.com/servicedesk/managing-customers-660967473.html
Under "Enabling request participants" the steps leads user to an option which is not available on the latest JIRA Service Desk.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2341].
  {panel}

At present, all internal comments are visible by all agents and collaborators. 

However, we have different standards of agents/collaborators. Both technical and business ones. Therefore, we require the capability to restrict internal comments to certain groups of collaborators, ie: restrict to technical only as a business collaborator has no requirement or need to see that comment.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2338].
  {panel}

h3. Summary
As per our [Adding people to participate in requests documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/SERVICEDESK/Adding+people+to+participate+in+requests#Addingpeopletoparticipateinrequests-Toaddrequestparticipantsviaemail:]:
{panel}Note that email recipients in the TO and BCC fields will not be added as request participants. {panel}

However, there might be cases where we need these emails to be added as request participant. Example:
* Customers are the one who requires input from 3rd parties and as they are not familiar with Service Desk, they will simply add these 3rd parties in the TO field, not CC.

h3. Suggestion
Make it a project level configurable option whether or not to add the emails found in the TO field in emails as Request Participants. However, keep JSD-2298 in mind where it might cause a Mail Loop

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-2337].
